From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nikami Worlds <nikami@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 22:20:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] esm4: gate native actor basis half-turn

Status: failed experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Depends-On: 0006-esm4-live-rig-bounds-telemetry.patch, 0007-esm4-part-matrix-runtime-audit-gate.patch

Recover a narrow piece of the local HIGGS-lite FNV truth-rig branch without
promoting the old branch wholesale. When OPENMW_ESM4_DISABLE_NATIVE_ACTOR_BASIS
or OPENMW_FNV_DISABLE_NATIVE_ACTOR_BASIS is set, native NIF controller sampling
does not apply the Fallout actor half-turn/bind rotation basis. Manual actor
animation sampling uses the same no-native-basis path for NifOsg keyframe
controllers.

Result: failed in run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-222230. FO3 still rendered
an inverted/disassembled actor and FNV produced no native screenshots with a
crash dump. The patch was reversed and the active catalog env gate was removed.
---
 apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp     | 27 +++++++++++++++++++++++----
 components/nifosg/controller.cpp       | 27 ++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 components/nifosg/controller.hpp       |  2 ++
 3 files changed, 47 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp b/apps/openmw/mwrender/animation.cpp
